	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">MottZilla wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">From everything I've heard you can leave the pin floating, you don't have to ground it. I've never really heard a good reason for why you'd want to ground it rather than just leave it not connected.</div>
<br />
<br />Correct- you CAN leave the pin floating.  It has an internal pulldown on it.  So cut your pin 4's and be happy <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /> 
<br />
<br />Cutting pin 4 will turn the lock into a key, which completely disables it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


