	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>kevtris</b> [ Fri Aug 31, 2007 4:02 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Jeroen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If  you really wanted you could desolder it and solder two wires for the reset. But it's just inpractical.</div>
<br />
<br />It won't work.  You have to invert the reset line for it to function properly (the button is active high, the /RST line is active low).   By far easier to simply cut pin 4.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


